using certbot certificate management (lets encrypt) for secure connection.
https://certbot.eff.org/instructions?ws=nginx&os=snap




1. SSH into your ec2 machine and make sure nginx is running.
2. Install Certbot:     sudo snap install --classic certbot
    Run this command on the command line on the machine to install Certbot.

3. Prepare the Certbot command
    Execute the following instruction on the command line on the machine to ensure that the certbot command can be run.
    sudo ln -s /snap/bin/certbot /usr/local/bin/certbot

4. run:    sudo certbot --nginx
    select all or selected domains for which you need certificate

certbot automatically modify the nginx conf to listen on https port 443.
for http port 80 itll automatically redirect to 443.